<MainLayout title="Manuscript Transcription (HTR)">
  <h1>II. Manuscript Transcription (HTR)</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-slate-500 -mt-4 mb-8 font-sans">Handwritten Text Recognition</p>

  <p>
    Handwritten Text Recognition (HTR) has emerged as one of the most transformative applications
    of AI in digital humanities, enabling researchers to process vast archives of historical
    documents at unprecedented speeds.
  </p>

  <h2>The CoMMA Project</h2>

  <p>
    The <strong>Computational Methods for Medieval Archives (CoMMA)</strong> project has demonstrated
    the remarkable potential of AI-powered transcription at scale.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Achievement</strong>: Transcribed 32,763 medieval manuscripts in just four months (January 2026)</li>
    <li><strong>Scope</strong>: Covers documents spanning multiple centuries, languages, and scribal traditions</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    This achievement would have taken human scholars decades to accomplish, representing a
    fundamental shift in how we can approach large-scale archival research.
  </p>

  <h2>Transkribus Platform</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>Transkribus</strong> has established itself as the dominant platform for HTR work in
    the humanities community.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Key Advantage</strong>: Avoids the "hallucinations" common in large language models</li>
    <li><strong>Methodology</strong>: Purpose-built for historical document processing rather than general text generation</li>
    <li><strong>Community</strong>: Supports collaborative model training across institutions</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Unlike general-purpose AI systems, Transkribus is specifically designed to transcribe what
    exists on the page without inventing or interpolating missing content—a critical distinction
    for scholarly work.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose my-10 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 rounded-r-lg">
    <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-slate-800 mb-2">Key Takeaway</h3>
    <p class="text-slate-700">
      HTR technology is revolutionizing archival access, but the choice of platform matters—
      purpose-built tools like Transkribus offer crucial accuracy guarantees that general AI
      systems cannot match.
    </p>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
